    • Method Detail

      • parse

        public BuildTarget parse(String buildTargetName,
                ParseContext parseContext)
                  throws NoSuchBuildTargetException
        Parameters:
        buildTargetName - either a fully-qualified name or relative to the ParseContext. For example, inside first-party/orca/orcaapp/BUILD, which can be obtained by calling ParseContext.forBaseName("first-party/orca/orcaapp"), //first-party/orca/orcaapp:assets and :assets refer to the same target. However, from the command line the context is obtained by calling ParseContext.fullyQualified() and relative names are not recognized.
        parseContext - how targets should be interpreted, such in the context of a specific build file or only as fully-qualified names (as is the case for targets from the command line).
        Throws:
        NoSuchBuildTargetException
